io.jenetics.prog.op

Class Const<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.jenetics.prog.op.Const<T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Op<T>, Function<T[],T>, Supplier<Op<T>>

    public final class Const<T>
extends Object
implements Op<T>
    Represents an operation which always returns the same, constant, value. To improve readability, constants may have a name. If a name is given, this name is used when printing the program tree.
    final static Op<Double> PI = Const.of("π", Math.PI); final static Op<Double> ONE = Const.of(1.0);
    Since:
    3.9
    Version:
    3.9
    Author:
